Harry Hornby Goodall (17 January 1877 – 20 February 1961) was an English cricketer.  Goodall was a right-handed batsman.  He was born at Nottingham, Nottinghamshire.
Goodall made his first-class debut for Nottinghamshire against Leicestershire in the 1902 County Championship.  He played a further fixture in that season against Essex.  He next played first-class cricket for the county in the 1905 County Championship, making three appearances against Essex, Middlesex and Derbyshire.  In his total of five first-class appearances for the county, he scored a total of 92 runs at an average of 15.33, with a high score of 26.He died at Beeston, Nottinghamshire, on 20 February 1961.
